item.title: Step 1 - Lets Talk
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
To get things going we will need to discuss your project. Providing me with the size, timeframe, and a general or specific description of your idea are a good start to a great mural.

Phone me @ 832-457-0657 or
e-mail me: david@davidcobbmurals.com

item.title: Step 2 - Site Visit
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is a chance for us to meet and discussthe project at the planned site/space. This meeting also gives me a chance to see how the painting will be incorporated into theexisting space and give me a chance to takea few photographs.

After the visit I will complete a few roughsketches that I will send along with an estimatefor the project. Usually I have that ready in a dayor two.

item.title: Step 3 - Drawings
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Once the estimate has been approved and Imgiven the green light, I will begin creatingdrawings. I will e-mail them to you as they arecompleted upon which you will review themand let me know what changes you would liketo make. We continue this process until weagree on the drawings.All work to be paintedwill be drawn first and approved before workbegins.

item.title: Step 4 - Lets Paint
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Once a timeline is established and the drawingsare complete, its time to paint! A 50% depositis collected before work begins and the remainingis due upon completion.

For pricing and availablity please contact me:
david@davidcobbmurals.com
832-457-0657

item.title: THE BASIC PROCESS
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The path to a great mural is not complicated, but it does require a fair amount of preparation. Depending on the project lead time can be as quick as a week, while larger projects can take a few months. As always, I consider the process to be a collaborative effortand I always encourage input from my clients. The more ideas the better!

item.title: ABOUT
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
David Cobb Murals got its first project back in2003 painting a 4x 8 sheet of plywood for my neighborhood swim team, The Willow Wahoos! It was a small project and it wasnt officially David Cobb Murals yet, but I was hookedto painting outside the studio.

Ive always been a painter. Whether it was myparents house, my nieghbors fence, or artclasses, painting has been my thing. I grew uplearning handy man skills and worked formany years with professional contract paintersmopping and gloping paint for commercialprojects. Those skills have been a great aid inthe quality of my work and efficiency on largeprojects.

With an emphasis in painting, I earned mybachelors degree from the University of Houstonand have been painting consistantly since. I remember being asked by one of my teachersupon graduation what I planned to do next. Ialready knew, paint murals.

Ive had amazing response over the years for mywork. I take a lot of pride in it and alwayswant the next project to be my best! Whetherpainting animated characters for a pre-schoolor a highly rendered city scape for a modelrailroad, there's nothing Id rather be doing thanpainting. Lets bring your ideas to life!
